@fredfinks If there was something cringey in the movie, that would be the Rev-9 and that worthless wannabe replacement for John Connor, Reyes-whatever her name is.
Linda played it pretty well. If you compare it directly with her T2 reprisal, I have some bad news for you, sonny: T2 can never be topped and we have to accept that.
Neither Arnold, nor Linda can ever impress at the same level they did back in 1991.

@katarn0329 In my personal opinion Genisys was doing a 9/10 for the first hour of the movie's runtime. I actually enjoyed the premise of Pops taking care of Sarah as a father figure. Daenerys was acceptable as Sarah Connor, but Reese.... wasn't a good cast. Jay Courtney looks nothing like a man out of a future where you have to feed on rats. 

The movie went downhill right after John Connor turned into the T-3000 and messed up the entire timeline the movie had built until that point. 

Action was top notch, though. And I'm always pleased to see Arnold enjoying his role and knocking it out the park as the T-800.

